# """
# eWaSR single-file adaptation for the user's training pipeline.
#
# Source repository:
# https://github.com/tersekmatija/eWaSR
#
# What is kept 1:1 from the original repo:
# - IntermediateLayerGetter
# - AttentionRefinementModule
# - FeatureFusionModule
# - ASPPv2Conv / ASPPv2
# - Spade / Bottleneck / NonBottleneck1DBlk / ResBlk / C3Blk / Conv / SPP
# - SpatialAttentionRefinementModule / PyramidPoolAgg / SIM / SegHead
# - Mlp / Pooling / Attention / ARMMixer / SpatialAttentionMixer / MetaFormerBlock
# - NoIMUDecoder / IMUDecoder / IMUDecoderSmall / EWaSRDecoder
# - the original WaSR core forward structure used by eWaSR
#
# What is adapted minimally so it can be trained by the user's train.py:
# - all dependent components are merged into one file
# - the public class exposed to archs is `EWaSR`
# - input is a plain tensor [B, C, H, W] instead of a dict {"image": ..., "imu_mask": ...}
# - output is logits tensor [B, num_classes, H, W] by default
# - optional support for deep_supervision returns [logits]
# - default path disables IMU because the user's dataloader only provides images
# - the original repo hard-codes EWaSRDecoder(num_classes=3); here it is adapted to the requested `num_classes`
#   so the model can be trained on the user's 8-class task with the unified pipeline
# - final logits are resized back to input spatial size for compatibility with the user's loss/metric code
# """
